[30;1m401 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m403 | [0m[35mallows storage implementations, like `NEO <http://www.neoppod.org/>`_,[0m
[30;1m404 | [0m[35mto support multiple transactions committing at the same time, for[0m

[30;1m406 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m2253 | [0m[35mZEO protocol and compatibility[0m
[30;1m2254 | [0m[35m------------------------------[0m
[30;1m2255 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m2256 | [0m[35mZODB 3.3 introduced multiversion concurrency control (MVCC), which required[0m
[30;1m2257 | [0m[35mchanges to the ZEO protocol.  The first 3.3 release should have increased[0m
[30;1m2258 | [0m[35mthe internal ZEO protocol version number (used by ZEO protocol negotiation[0m

[30;1m1951 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m1952 | [0m[35m- (3.4a3) Transaction objects have a new method, ``beforeCommitHook(hook,[0m
[30;1m1953 | [0m[35m  *args, **kws)``.  Hook functions registered with a transaction are called[0m
[30;1m1954 | [0m[35m  at the start of a top-level commit, before any of the work is begun, so a[0m
[30;1m1955 | [0m[35m  hook function can perform any database operations it likes.  See[0m
[30;1m1956 | [0m[35m  ``test_beforeCommitHook()`` in ``transaction/tests/test_transaction.py``[0m
[30;1m1957 | [0m[35m  for a tutorial doctest, and the ``ITransaction`` interface for details.[0m

[30;1m3578 | [0m[35mThe ZEO server has an optional timeout feature that will abort a[0m
[30;1m3579 | [0m[35mconnection that does not commit within a certain amount of time.  The[0m
[30;1m3580 | [0m[35mtimeout works by closing the socket the client is using, causing both[0m
[30;1m3581 | [0m[35mclient and server to abort the transaction and continue.  This is a[0m
[30;1m3582 | [0m[35mdrastic step, but can be useful to prevent a hung client or other bug[0m
[30;1m3583 | [0m[35mfrom blocking a server indefinitely.[0m

[30;1m1326 | [0m[35m  Python's cyclic garbage collection can take "a long time" to reclaim them[0m
[30;1m1327 | [0m[35m  (and may in fact never reclaim them if application code keeps strong[0m
[30;1m1328 | [0m[35m  references to them), but such forgotten connections can never be opened[0m
[30;1m1329 | [0m[35m  again, so their caches are now cleared at the time ``DB`` forgets them.[0m
[30;1m1330 | [0m[35m  Most applications won't notice a difference, but applications that open[0m
[30;1m1331 | [0m[35m  many connections, and/or store many large objects in connection caches,[0m
[30;1m1332 | [0m[35m  and/or store limited resources (such as RDB connections) in connection[0m

[30;1m617 | [0m[35m  tended to cause the same connection(s) to be used over and over.[0m
[30;1m618 | [0m[35m  For example, the most used connection would typically be the only[0m
[30;1m619 | [0m[35m  connection used.  In some rare situations, extra connections could[0m
[30;1m620 | [0m[35m  be opened and end up on the top of the stack, causing extreme memory[0m
[30;1m621 | [0m[35m  wastage.  Now, when connections are placed on the stack, they sink[0m
[30;1m622 | [0m[35m  below existing connections that have more active objects.[0m
[30;1m623 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m609 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m610 | [0m[35m- The FileStorage iterator now handles large files better.  When[0m
[30;1m611 | [0m[35m  iterating from a starting transaction near the end of the file, the[0m
[30;1m612 | [0m[35m  iterator will scan backward from the end of the file to find the[0m
[30;1m613 | [0m[35m  starting point.  This enhancement makes it practical to take[0m
[30;1m614 | [0m[35m  advantage of the new storage server invalidation-age option.[0m
[30;1m615 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m605 | [0m[35m  than a given time even if the number of transactions the client[0m

[30;1m608 | [0m[35m  from a point near the end of the transaction history.[0m

[30;1m394 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m395 | [0m[35mZODB supports concurrency through transactions.  Multiple programs[0m
[30;1m396 | [0m[35m[#wtf-program]_ can operate independently in separate transactions.[0m
[30;1m397 | [0m[35mThey synchronize at transaction boundaries.[0m
[30;1m398 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m399 | [0m[35mThe most common way to run ZODB is with each program running in its[0m
[30;1m400 | [0m[35mown thread.  Usually the thread-local transaction manager is used.[0m

[30;1m76 | [0m[35m   Transaction managers create transactions and[0m
[30;1m77 | [0m[35m   provide APIs to start and end transactions.  The transactions[0m
[30;1m78 | [0m[35m   managed are always sequential. There is always exactly one active[0m

[30;1m46 | [0m[35mIn the example above, we used ``transaction.commit()`` to commit a[0m
[30;1m47 | [0m[35mtransaction, making the change to ``conn.root`` permanent.  This is[0m

[30;1m387 | [0m[35m            # returns (), but we don't want to have to deghostify[0m
[30;1m388 | [0m[35m            # the object to find out.[0m
[30;1m389 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m390 | [0m[35m            # Note that this has the odd effect that, if the class has[0m
[30;1m391 | [0m[35m            # __getnewargs__ of its own, we'll lose the optimization[0m

[30;1m16 | [0m[35mZODB serializes objects using a custom format based on Python pickles.[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35mWhen an object is unserialized, it can be loaded as either a ghost or[0m
[30;1m18 | [0m[35ma real object.  A ghost is a persistent object of the appropriate type[0m
[30;1m19 | [0m[35mbut without any state.  The first time a ghost is accessed, the[0m
[30;1m20 | [0m[35mpersistence machinery traps access and loads the actual state.  A[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35mghost allows many persistent objects to be loaded while minimizing the[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35mmemory consumption of referenced but otherwise unused objects.[0m

   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m184 | [0m[35m------------[0m
[30;1m185 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m186 | [0m[35mA Connection keeps objects in its cache so that multiple database[0m
[30;1m187 | [0m[35mreferences will always point to the same Python object.  At[0m
[30;1m188 | [0m[35mtransaction boundaries, objects modified by other transactions are[0m
[30;1m189 | [0m[35mghostified so that the next transaction doesn't see stale state.  We[0m
[30;1m190 | [0m[35mneed to be sure the non-current objects loaded by MVCC are always[0m

[30;1m37 | [0m[35m------------[0m

[30;1m39 | [0m[35mThe ZODB has a transactional support at its core. Transactions provide[0m
[30;1m40 | [0m[35mconcurrency control and atomicity. Transactions are executed as if they have[0m
[30;1m41 | [0m[35mexclusive access to the data, so as an application developer you don’t have to[0m
[30;1m42 | [0m[35mworry about threading. Of course there is nothing to prevent two simultaneous[0m
[30;1m43 | [0m[35mconflicting requests, So checks are made at transaction commit time to ensure[0m

[30;1m36 | [0m[35mTransactions[0m
[30;1m37 | [0m[35m------------[0m
[30;1m38 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m39 | [0m[35mThe ZODB has a transactional support at its core. Transactions provide[0m
[30;1m40 | [0m[35mconcurrency control and atomicity. Transactions are executed as if they have[0m
[30;1m41 | [0m[35mexclusive access to the data, so as an application developer you don’t have to[0m
[30;1m42 | [0m[35mworry about threading. Of course there is nothing to prevent two simultaneous[0m

[30;1m389 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m390 | [0m[35mWorse, a :meth:`__del__` method can interfere with the persistence machinery's[0m
[30;1m391 | [0m[35mgoals.  For example, some number of persistent objects reside in a[0m
[30;1m392 | [0m[35m:class:`Connection`'s memory cache.  At various times, to reduce memory burden,[0m
[30;1m393 | [0m[35mobjects that haven't been referenced recently are removed from the cache.  If a[0m
[30;1m394 | [0m[35mpersistent object with a :meth:`__del___` method is so removed, and the cache[0m
[30;1m395 | [0m[35mwas holding the last memory reference to the object, the object's[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m994[0m[34m of [0m[33m1177[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m340 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m341 | [0m[35mZODB allows persistent classes to have hook methods like :meth:`__getattr__` and[0m
[30;1m342 | [0m[35m:meth:`__setattr__`.  There are four special methods that control attribute[0m
[30;1m343 | [0m[35maccess; the rules for each are a little different.[0m
[30;1m344 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m345 | [0m[35mThe :meth:`__getattr__` method works pretty much the same for persistent classes[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m995[0m[34m of [0m[33m1177[0m[31m ]--[0m

  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m

[30;1m285 | [0m[35m  time it is used.  Since the Python interpreter is unaware of persistence, it[0m
[30;1m286 | [0m[35m  would call :meth:`__del__` each time the object was freed.[0m

[30;1m282 | [0m[35m* A persistent class should not have a :meth:`__del__` method. The database[0m
[30;1m283 | [0m[35m  moves objects freely between memory and storage.  If an object has not been used[0m
[30;1m284 | [0m[35m  in a while, it may be released and its contents loaded from storage the next[0m
[30;1m285 | [0m[35m  time it is used.  Since the Python interpreter is unaware of persistence, it[0m
[30;1m286 | [0m[35m  would call :meth:`__del__` each time the object was freed.[0m
[30;1m287 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m288 | [0m[35mLet's look at each of these rules in detail.[0m

[30;1m184 | [0m[35mmeans that the operation has to be retried; other applications might treat it as[0m

[30;1m209 | [0m[35m:meth:`new_messages` introduces the use of *volatile* attributes.  Attributes of[0m
[30;1m210 | [0m[35ma persistent object that begin with ``_v_`` are considered volatile and are[0m
[30;1m211 | [0m[35mnever stored in the database.  :meth:`new_messages` needs to store the last time[0m
[30;1m212 | [0m[35mthe method was called, but if the time was stored as a regular attribute, its[0m
[30;1m213 | [0m[35mvalue would be committed to the database and shared with all the other clients.[0m
[30;1m214 | [0m[35m:meth:`new_messages` would then return the new messages accumulated since any[0m
[30;1m215 | [0m[35mother client called :meth:`new_messages`, which isn't what we want. ::[0m
